The paper presents a numerical scheme for computing Artificial Neural Networks' weights, which is highly efficient and results in low errors for regression and classification of complex data-sets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to the MNIST database for handwritten digits recognition, which falls under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the numerical solution of Partial Differential Equations, which suggests that it may belong to the Scientific Computing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the elimination of overfitting and the interpretability of results, which are important topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
